# Security baseline

- Validate type, format, length, and range at every boundary
- No secrets, tokens, or connection strings in code or logs
- Parameterized queries / prepared statements only
- Principle of least privilege for keys and service accounts
- Rate-limit auth endpoints
- Fail closed on authorization errors
- Mask PII in logs

For security-sensitive changes, recommend optional catalog skill: `jeffallan/claude-skills@security-reviewer` via `install-catalog-skill.ps1`.
